877
01:36:09,180 --> 01:36:10,238
Nowhere to go, son.

878
01:36:21,292 --> 01:36:23,055
Run, boy.

879
01:36:23,227 --> 01:36:24,751
Run, August, run.

880
01:36:45,883 --> 01:36:48,351
August!

881
01:37:38,469 --> 01:37:40,994
August!

882
01:38:01,358 --> 01:38:03,986
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

883
01:38:04,361 --> 01:38:10,163
Music has always fascinated us
in the way that it communicates.

884
01:38:10,334 --> 01:38:13,360
Without words, without pictures.

885
01:38:14,271 --> 01:38:17,138
And that leads us
to our final performance.

886
01:38:21,312 --> 01:38:23,473
How much longer to the airport?

887
01:38:23,647 --> 01:38:26,138
Man, it jams up the traffic.

888
01:38:26,317 --> 01:38:28,808
Bring you back to the old days,
eh, Louis?

889
01:38:46,537 --> 01:38:48,334
"August Rush."

890
01:38:48,505 --> 01:38:50,336
Evan Taylor.

891
01:39:06,056 --> 01:39:10,720
Unfortunately, our last performer
seems to have...

892
01:39:10,894 --> 01:39:13,761
He's here. He's here. He's here.

893
01:39:15,165 --> 01:39:16,257
Excellent.

894
01:39:16,433 --> 01:39:23,362
Perhaps there's no one else who can
better personify the mystery that is music...

895
